{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure is at an external contract boundary: embedding provider output dimension vs index schema. A mock embedding client can hide real model/version drift and always pass. REAL-INFRA applies because catching provider-side dimensional mismatch requires a real API call. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: behavior checks shape compatibility, not output quality or multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end API test against the real embedding endpoint configured for production and a real index schema; submit a query and assert returned embedding length equals index dimension before/at upsert/search boundary.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is primarily module handoff/ordering logic between search service and vector-store adapter. It can be caught by wiring real local modules with a controlled corpus and known vectors/scores. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no required real OS/network/subprocess in behavior text, (b) no AI quality dependence, (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejected System because behavior text only requires ordering correctness, not real network/vector SaaS behavior.","test_description":"Create a deterministic test dataset in a local/in-process vector store fixture, run similarity search through service + repository layers, and assert returned items are strictly sorted by descending cosine similarity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The LLM re-ranking step changes the order of at least some results compared to the raw similarity ranking when the query has nuanced intent.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM semantic judgment for nuanced intent; deterministic stubs can trivially reorder and hide true relevance failures. LLM-DEP applies directly, and outcomes may vary run-to-run. Rejected Workflow: this behavior targets one agentic step (re-ranking) relative to an existing baseline list, not validation of a full multi-agentic pipeline.","test_description":"Execute reranking with the real LLM on curated nuanced queries and candidate lists; compare raw similarity order vs reranked order and assert at least one meaningful rank change occurs on designated cases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A query with no close matches in the database returns an empty result set rather than low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is a relevance-quality boundary: deciding that a query has no close semantic neighbors depends on embedding/model behavior and score distribution, which mocks can mask. A deterministic fake can force empties and miss real false-positive noise. Rejected Workflow: behavior is a single decision outcome for one query path, not multiple real agentic steps chained.","test_description":"Run the real embedding+search path on a benchmark set of out-of-domain/no-match queries against a fixed corpus; assert API returns empty results when top similarity stays below the configured relevance threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.56,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This explicitly measures full pipeline latency across multiple sequential agentic calls (embedding + LLM rerank) plus vector retrieval. MULTI-STEP applies, and real infra timing effects (network/API latency) matter; mocks would understate tail/median latency and hide regressions.","test_description":"Run production-like load test on the full API pipeline with real embedding service, real vector DB, and real LLM reranker; collect end-to-end latency over representative query mix and assert p50 < 2.0s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
